Certainly! Below is a script that creates a form which accepts and saves user-inputted text related to the production and application of tetraethyl lead (TEL).

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tetraethyl Lead Production and Application Form</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .form-container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        input, textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 3px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="form-container">
    <h2>Tetraethyl Lead Production and Application Form</h2>
    <form id="telForm">
        <label for="productionProcess">Production Process:</label>
        <textarea id="productionProcess" name="productionProcess" rows="5" required></textarea>

        <label for="applicationProcess">Application Process:</label>
        <textarea id="applicationProcess" name="applicationProcess" rows="5" required></textarea>

        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <div id="confirmationMessage" style="margin-top: 20px; color: green;"></div>
</div>

<script>
    document.getElementById('telForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
        event.preventDefault();

        const productionProcess = document.getElementById('productionProcess').value;
        const applicationProcess = document.getElementById('applicationProcess').value;

        if (productionProcess && applicationProcess) {
            // Save the data (for demonstration, we'll just log it to the console)
            console.log("Production Process:", productionProcess);
            console.log("Application Process:", applicationProcess);

            // Display confirmation message
            document.getElementById('confirmationMessage').innerText = "Form submitted successfully!";
        } else {
            alert("Please fill out all fields.");
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **HTML Structure:**
   - A form is created with two textareas: one for the production process and another for the application process.
   - A submit button is included to submit the form.

2. **CSS Styling:**
   - Basic styling is applied to make the form visually appealing and user-friendly.

3. **JavaScript Functionality:**
   - An event listener is added to the form to handle the submission.
   - When the form is submitted, the JavaScript code prevents the default form submission behavior.
   - It retrieves the values from the textareas and logs them to the console.
   - A confirmation message is displayed to inform the user that the form has been submitted successfully.

This script provides a simple yet functional form for users to input and save information about the production and application of tetraethyl lead.

